transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling customer service. I can help you.

Speaker 2: Yes, hi. I have a problem and I sent some emails and I've been trying to get through and this is the first time I actually was able to get through. I actually ordered the product Score Blue and it gave me kind of hot flashes and stuff, my nose up pretty bad.

Speaker 1: So you wrote them about it and they said to try a little lower dose?

Speaker 2: Yes, but I did and it didn't help me. So I canceled the order. Then all of a sudden, a couple of days ago on Friday, I seen the charge.

Speaker 1: So you tried to call but obviously you didn't get through, and then the weekend and yesterday you couldn't get through?

Speaker 2: Right. But actually, the email I wrote them, I said I canceled and the girl in the email told me to call this number and you could cancel over the phone, but I was already charged.

Speaker 1: Okay, what's your zip code?

Speaker 2: 10465.

Speaker 1: And your name's Lewis Bartolotti?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay, I have your account up here. What did you want to do?

Speaker 2: Well, I did cancel the item weeks ago and all of a sudden I noticed that I got a charge. So when I sent the email about the charge, they told me that I had to call this number and you guys will take care of it.

Speaker 1: Okay, and what are we taking?

Speaker 2: What? I'm sorry, so you want us to—

Speaker 1: You want to return the package that's on the way to you?

Speaker 2: I never got the package. I only got charged.

Speaker 1: Wow. Now what do I do? I can't—I can't even—I have the rest of the pills left from the lesson.

Speaker 2: I can't take them and I actually called.

Speaker 1: Really? Okay, I'll keep them in the same package. How do I send them back?

Speaker 2: You just don't open it and give it back to the mail person.

Speaker 1: Well, that's gonna be hard for me to do unless I see him.

Speaker 2: Drop it off at the mail, at the USPS.

Speaker 1: If I—without a return—

Speaker 2: Or anything.

Speaker 1: Yes, you'll use the same—

Speaker 2: The same.

Speaker 1: The same postage, don't open it and drop it back off. Okay, and then when you get it back, you'll credit me?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay. Thank you very much.

Speaker 2: Please.

Speaker 1: Yeah, thank you.

Speaker 2: Have a nice day.
